problem_text_en:
An elevator is ascending with an acceleration of $1.22 \, \text{m/s}^2$. When its upward speed is $2.44 \, \text{m/s}$, a nut falls loose from the elevator's ceiling. The distance between the ceiling and the floor of the elevator is $2.74 \, \text{m}$. Calculate:
1) The time it takes for the nut to fall from the ceiling to the floor;
2) The displacement and the distance traveled by the nut relative to a fixed pillar outside the elevator.
